# Key Insights & Business Recommendations

## Project: End-to-End Marketing Funnel Analysis
**Author:** Ajith_Settu | **Period:** Q1 2024 |


## 1. Funnel Health Overview

| Stage             | Count | Conversion Rate |
|-------------------|-------|-----------------|
| Total Leads       | 30    | —               |
| MQL               | 28    | 93.3%           |
| SQL               | 15    | 53.6%           |
| Opportunity       | 9     | 60.0%           |
| Closed Won        | 5     | 55.6%           |
| **Overall Win Rate** | **5** | **16.7%**   |

**Key Insight:** The biggest drop-off is at the MQL → SQL stage (53.6%), indicating that while marketing is generating strong top-of-funnel volume, sales qualification is filtering out nearly half. This could reflect targeting quality or BDR capacity issues.


## 2. Best Performing Lead Sources

| Source          | Win Rate |
|-----------------|----------|
| Referral        | 33.3%    |
| Paid Search     | 25.0%    |
| Organic Search  | 12.5%    |
| Email           | 0%       |
| Social Media    | 0%       |

**Recommendation:** Double down on referral programs and paid search. Email and social media generate volume but show lower funnel progression — review nurture sequences for these segments.


## 3. Email Campaign Performance

| Segment         | Open Rate | CTR   | Bounce Rate |
|-----------------|-----------|-------|-------------|
| SaaS Leads      | ~30%      | 8.5%  | 4.1%        |
| Ecommerce Leads | ~27%      | 7.9%  | 4.1%        |
| FinTech Leads   | ~33%      | 9.0%  | 3.1%        |

**Key Insight:** FinTech segment shows the highest open and click rates despite smaller send volume — a signal of strong audience relevance. SaaS Nurture Wave 3 shows declining CTR vs Wave 1, suggesting content fatigue.

**Recommendation:** A/B test FinTech-style subject lines on SaaS campaigns. Refresh content for Wave 3+ sends to reduce engagement decay.


## 4. Sales Cycle Velocity

| Stage Transition     | Avg Days |
|----------------------|----------|
| MQL → SQL            | ~6 days  |
| SQL → Opportunity    | ~8 days  |
| Opportunity → Close  | ~17 days |
| **Total Cycle**      | **~31 days** |

**Key Insight:** The Opportunity → Close stage takes the longest. This is a negotiation/decision-making bottleneck. Referral leads close ~20% faster than cold inbound.

**Recommendation:** Introduce automated follow-up sequences for opportunities open > 14 days to reduce stall time.


## 5. Cohort Performance

| Cohort     | Size | Win Rate |
|------------|------|----------|
| 2024-01    | 15   | 20.0%    |
| 2024-02    | 10   | 10.0%    |
| 2024-03    | 5    | 0% (too early) |

**Key Insight:** January cohort performs best — aligns with strong Q1 campaign launches. March cohort is too recent to show wins (longer sales cycle expected).


## 6. Stalled Leads in Pipeline

Several leads with active funnel stages (MQL/SQL/Opportunity) show no activity in 14+ days. These represent revenue at risk and candidates for re-engagement campaigns.

**Recommendation:** Build an automated weekly SQL report to flag stalled leads for BDR re-outreach or marketing nurture re-entry.


## Tools & Skills Demonstrated

- **Window Functions:** `FIRST_VALUE()`, `OVER (PARTITION BY ... ORDER BY ...)`
- **CTEs:** Used across all queries for readable, layered logic
- **Conditional Aggregation:** `CASE WHEN ... THEN ... END` inside `COUNT/SUM`
- **Date Math:** `JULIANDAY()` for stage velocity calculations
- **NULLIF:** Safe division to prevent divide-by-zero errors
- **JOINs:** LEFT JOIN for funnel inclusion, INNER JOIN for conversion-only views
- **Business Metrics:** CTR, open rate, CTOR, bounce rate, MQL/SQL/win rates, cohort analysis
